51.6	Tourmaline	Tourmaline	Tourmaline is a crystal boron silicate mineral compounded with elements such as aluminium, iron, magnesium, sodium, lithium, or potassium. Tourmaline is classified as a semi-precious stone and the gem comes in a wide variety of colors. The name comes from the Sinhalese word "Thuramali" (තුරමලි) or "Thoramalli" (තෝරමල්ලි), which applied to different gemstones found in Sri Lanka.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/TourmalineUSGOV.jpg/240px-TourmalineUSGOV.jpg
